Lonmin Says Second-Quarter Tons Mined Increased 10.4% From a Year Earlier

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-05-09T06:02:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/lonmin-says-second-quarter-tons-mined-increased-10-4-from-a-year-earlier.html
Lonmin Plc (LMI) , the third-largest platinum
producer, said overall total tons mined during the second-
quarter increased by 10.4 percent from a year earlier.  Lonmin commented in a stock exchange statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  